msgid ""
"In addition to that, OTRS 7 also requires an active cluster of Elasticsearch "
"6.0 or higher. Please refer to the <link linkend=\"installation-setup-"
"elasticsearch-cluster\">Setup Elasticsearch Cluster</link> section in the "
"installation guide."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:177
msgid "Step 4: Run the migration script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:181
msgid ""
"If you have any custom Perl or XML configuration files in <filename>Kernel/"
"Config/Files</filename>, these need to be <ulink url=\"http://doc.otrs.com/"
"doc/manual/developer/6.0/en/html/package-porting.html#packge-porting-5-to-6-"
"configuration-files\">converted to the new formats supported by OTRS 7</"
"ulink> before running the migration script."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:187
msgid ""
"The migration script will perform many checks on your system and give you "
"advice on how to install missing Perl modules etc., if that is required. If "
"all checks succeeded, the necessary migration steps will be performed. "
"Please also run this script in case of patch level updates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:193
msgid ""
"Run the migration script (as user <literal>otrs</literal>, NOT as "
"<literal>root</literal>):"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"otrs> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"otrs> scripts/DBUpdate-to-7.pl\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><warning><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:205
msgid ""
"Do not continue the upgrading process if this script did not work properly "
"for you.  Otherwise malfunction or data loss may occur."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:212
msgid "Step 5: Update installed packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:215
msgid ""
"Packages for OTRS 6 are not compatible with OTRS 7 and have to be updated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:219
msgid ""
"You can use the command below to update all installed packages.  This works "
"for all packages that are available from online repositories.  You can "
"update other packages later via the package manager (this requires a running "
"OTRS Daemon)."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:223
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"otrs> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"otrs> bin/otrs.Console.pl Admin::Package::UpgradeAll\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:230
msgid "Step 6: Restart your services"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:233
msgid ""
"OTRS 7 comes with an own built-in web server that is used behind apache as a "
"reverse proxy (or any other reverse proxy server). For major updates from "
"OTRS 6, the apache configuration must be updated with the new version in "
"<filename>/opt/otrs/scripts/apache2-httpd.include.conf</filename>, if it was "
"copied and not just linked. Please also note that while mod_perl is no "
"longer needed, other Apache modules are required now: <literal>proxy_module</"
"literal>, <literal>proxy_http_module</literal> and "
"<literal>proxy_wstunnel_module</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:237
msgid ""
"After that, the services can be restarted.  This will depend on your service "
"configuration, here is an example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:242
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"root> /etc/init.d/apache start\n"
"root> /etc/init.d/postfix start\n"
"root> /etc/init.d/cron start\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:251
msgid ""
"The OTRS Daemon is required for correct operation of OTRS such as sending "
"emails.  Please activate it as described in the next step."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><title>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:258
msgid "Step 7: Start the OTRS Daemon, web server and cron job"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:261
msgid ""
"The OTRS Daemon is responsible for handling any asynchronous and recurring "
"tasks in OTRS.  The daemon and its keepalive cron job must be started as the "
"<literal>otrs</literal> user.  The built-in OTRS web server process handles "
"the web requests handed over from Apache."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:267
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"otrs> cd /opt/otrs/\n"
"otrs> bin/otrs.Daemon.pl start\n"
"otrs> bin/Cron.sh start\n"
"otrs> bin/otrs.WebServer.pl\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para>
#: en/content/installation/updating.xml:275
msgid "Now you can log into your system."
msgstr ""

