"all customer users (limited to <literal>CustomerUserSearchListLimit</"
"literal> property from the customer user backend). This option is "
"discouraged specially for systems with a large number of customer users as "
"it might require too much time to execute and depending on the limit it "
"might be possible that not all customer certificates will be fetch. Execute "
"the console command in this mode as: <placeholder type=\"screen\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:296
msgid ""
"For this option the console command will query the customer user backends to "
"get all possible customers and for each it will check if there is a S/MIME "
"certificate. If a certificate is found, it will try to add it to the system "
"(if the certificate is not already added)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:301
msgid "Renew existing certificates:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:304
msgid ""
"Another console command <literal>Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Renew</"
"literal> can be used to check for all existing certificates in the system. "
"This verifies that the existing certificates from customer users matches the "
"ones that are retrieved by the customer user properties. Any new certificate "
"in the customer user backend will be added into the system (no certificates "
"are deleted in this process)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:307
msgid ""
"This console command is executed once a day by the OTRS daemon automatically "
"with the task <literal>Daemon::SchedulerCronTaskManager::"
"Task###RenewCustomerSMIMECertificates</literal> (as seen in SysConfig), but "
"it can be also executed manually on demand as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/administration/email/smime.xml:310
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> perl /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Renew\n"
msgstr "shell> perl /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::SMIME::CustomerCertificate::Renew\n"

#. type: Content of: <preface><title>
#: en/content/preface.xml:6
msgid "Preface"
msgstr "Vorwort"

#. type: Content of: <preface><para>
#: en/content/preface.xml:9
msgid ""
"This book is intended for use by OTRS administrators. It also serves as a "
"good reference for OTRS newbies."
msgstr ""
"Dieses Buch soll das Leben von OTRS-Administratoren und -Neulingen "
"erleichtern."

#. type: Content of: <preface><para>
#: en/content/preface.xml:13
msgid ""
"The following chapters describe the installation, configuration, and "
"administration of the OTRS software. The first third of the text describes "
"key functionality of the software, while the remainder serves as a reference "
"to the full set of configurable parameters."
msgstr ""
"Die folgenden Kapitel beschreiben die Installation, Konfiguration und "
"Administration von OTRS. Das erste Drittel des Textes beschreibt die "
"Hauptfunktionalität der Software, während der Rest als Referenz aller "
"vorhandenen Konfigurationseinstellungen dient."

#. type: Content of: <preface><para>
#: en/content/preface.xml:17
msgid ""
"This book continues to be a work in progress, given a moving target on new "
"releases. We need your feedback in order to make this a high quality "
"reference document: one that is usable, accurate, and complete. Please write "
"to us if you find content missing in this book, if things are not explained "
"sufficiently, or even if you see spelling mistakes, grammatical errors, or "
"typos. Any kind of feedback is highly appreciated and should be made via our "
"bug tracking system on <ulink url=\"http://bugs.otrs.org\"> "
"<citetitle>http://bugs.otrs.org</citetitle> </ulink>.  Thanks in advance for "
"your contributions!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/content/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:6
msgid "Installation"
msgstr "Installation"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><abstract><para>
#: en/content/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:10
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "This chapter describes the backup and restore of the OTRS data."
msgid ""
"This chapter describes the installation and basic configuration of the "
"central OTRS framework."
msgstr ""
"In diesem Kapitel wird beschrieben, wie alle relevanten Daten der OTRS-"
"Installation gesichert und wieder hergestellt werden können."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><abstract><para>
#: en/content/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:14
msgid ""
"Follow the detailed steps in this chapter to install OTRS on your server. "
"You can then use its web interface to login and administer the system."
msgstr ""
"Folgen Sie den Schritten in diesem Kapitel, um OTRS auf Ihrem Server zu "
"installieren. Dann können Sie sich über die Weboberfläche anmelden und das "
"System administrieren."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:6
msgid "Performance Tuning"
msgstr "Leistungsverbesserung"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><abstract><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:10
msgid ""
"Presented below is a list of performance enhancing techniques for your OTRS "
"installation, including configuration, coding, memory use, and more."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:16
msgid "OTRS"
msgstr "OTRS"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:18
msgid "There are several options for improving OTRS performance."
msgstr "Es gibt verschiedene Ansätze zur Leistungssteigerung von OTRS."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:22
msgid "TicketIndexModule"
msgstr "TicketIndexModule"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:24
msgid "There are two backend modules for the index for the ticket queue view:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:28
msgid "<literal>Kernel::System::Ticket::IndexAccelerator::RuntimeDB</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:31
msgid ""
"This is the default option, and will generate each queue view on the fly "
"from the ticket table. You will not have performance trouble until you have "
"about 60,000 open tickets in your system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:38
msgid "<literal>Kernel::System::Ticket::IndexAccelerator::StaticDB</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:41
msgid ""
"The most powerful module, should be used when you have above 80,000 open "
"tickets. It uses an extra <literal>ticket_index</literal> table, which will "
"be populated with keywords based on ticket data. Use <filename>bin/otrs."
"Console.pl Maint::Ticket::QueueIndexRebuild</filename> for generating an "
"initial index after switching backends."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:51
msgid "You can change the used IndexAccelerator module via SysConfig."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:56
msgid "Ticket Search Index"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:58
msgid ""
"OTRS uses a special search index to perform full-text searches across fields "
"in articles from different communication channels."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:62
msgid ""
"To create an initial index, use <filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Ticket::"
"FulltextIndex --rebuild</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:67
msgid ""
"Actual article indexing happens via an OTRS daemon job in the background. "
"While articles which were just added in the system are marked for indexing "
"immediately, it could happen their index is available within a few minutes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:73
msgid "There are some options available for fine tuning the search index:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:77
msgid "<literal>Ticket::SearchIndex::IndexArchivedTickets</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:80
msgid ""
"Defines if archived tickets will be included in the search index (off by "
"default). This is advisable to keep the index small on large systems with "
"archived tickets. If this is turned off, archived tickets will not be found "
"by full-text searches."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:87
msgid "<literal>Ticket::SearchIndex::Attribute</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:90
msgid ""
"The attribute <literal>WordCountMax</literal> defines the maximum number of "
"words which will be processed to build up the index. For example only the "
"first 1000 words of an article body are stored in the article search index. "
"The attributes <literal>WordLengthMin</literal> and <literal>WordLengthMax</"
"literal> are used as word length boundaries. Only words with a length "
"between these two values are stored in the article search index."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:99
msgid "<literal>Ticket::SearchIndex::Filters</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:102
msgid "There are three default filters defined:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:107
msgid ""
"The first filter strips out special chars like: <literal>, &amp; &lt; &gt; ? "
"\" ! * | ; [ ] ( ) + $ ^=</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:113
msgid ""
"The second filter strips out words which begin or ends with one of following "
"chars: <literal>' : .</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:119
msgid ""
"The third filter strips out words which do not contain a word-character: "
"<literal>a-z, A-Z, 0-9, _</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:127
msgid "<literal>Ticket::SearchIndex::StopWords</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:130
msgid ""
"There are so-called stop-words defined for some languages. These stop-words "
"will be skipped while creating the search index."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:139
msgid "Article Storage (Email, Phone and Internal Articles)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:141
msgid ""
"There are two different backend modules for the article storage of phone, "
"email and internal articles (configured via <literal>Ticket::Article::"
"Backend::MIMEBase::ArticleStorage</literal>):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:146
msgid ""
"<literal>Kernel::System::Ticket::Article::Backend::MIMEBase::"
"ArticleStorageDB</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:149
msgid "This default module will store attachments in the database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><note><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:153
msgid "Don't use it with large setups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:157
msgid "Pro: works with multiple front end servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:160
msgid "Con: requires much storage space in the database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:165
msgid ""
"<literal>Kernel::System::Ticket::Article::Backend::MIMEBase::"
"ArticleStorageFS</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:168
msgid "Use this module to store attachments on the local file system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><note><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:172
msgid "Recommended for large setups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:176
msgid "Pro: It is fast!"
msgstr "Pro: Schneller!"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:179
msgid ""
"Con: If you have multiple front end servers, you must make sure the file "
"system is shared between the servers. Place it on an NFS share or preferably "
"a SAN or similar solution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:187
msgid ""
"You can switch from one back-end to the other on the fly. You can switch the "
"backend in the SysConfig, and then run the command line utility "
"<filename>bin/otrs.Console.pl Admin::Article::StorageSwitch</filename> to "
"put the articles from the database onto the filesystem or the other way "
"around. You can use the <emphasis>--target</emphasis> option to specify the "
"target backend. Please note that the entire process can take considerable "
"time to run, depending on the number of articles you have and the available "
"CPU power and/or network capacity."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Admin::Article::StorageSwitch --target ArticleStorageFS\n"
msgstr "shell> bin/otrs.Console.pl Admin::Article::StorageSwitch --target ArticleStorageFS\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:202
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Script: Switching storage back-ends from database to filesystem.</"
"emphasis>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Skript: Wechsel des TicketStorage-Backends von Datenbank zu "
"Dateisystem.</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:205
msgid ""
"If you want to keep old attachments in the database, you can activate the "
"SysConfig option <literal>Ticket::Article::Backend::MIMEBase::"
"CheckAllStorageBackends</literal> to make sure OTRS will still find them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:212
msgid "Archiving Tickets"
msgstr "Tickets archivieren"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:215
msgid ""
"As OTRS can be used as an audit-proof system, deleting closed tickets may "
"not be a good idea. Therefore we implemented a feature that allows you to "
"archive tickets."
msgstr ""
"Da OTRS als revisionssicheres System betrieben werden kann, ist das Löschen "
"von geschlossenen Tickets möglicherweise nicht empfehlenswert. Daher haben "
"wir eine Funktion implementiert, mit der Sie Tickets archivieren können."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:219
msgid ""
"Tickets that match certain criteria can be marked as \"archived\". These "
"tickets are not accessed if you do a regular ticket search or run a Generic "
"Agent job. The system itself does not have to deal with a huge amount of "
"tickets any longer as only the \"latest\" tickets are taken into "
"consideration when using OTRS. This can result in a huge performance gain on "
"large systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:225
msgid "To use the archive feature simply follow these steps:"
msgstr ""
"Befolgen Sie folgende Schritte, um die Archivierungsfunktion zu nutzen:"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:230
msgid "Activate the archive system in SysConfig"
msgstr "Archivsystem in der SysConfig aktivieren"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:233
msgid ""
"In the Admin page, go to SysConfig and select the group <literal>Ticket</"
"literal>. In <literal>Core::Ticket</literal> you find the option "
"<literal>Ticket::ArchiveSystem</literal> which is set to \"no\" by default. "
"Change this setting to \"yes\" and save this change."
msgstr ""
"Wählen Sie in der SysConfig die Gruppe <literal>Ticket</literal> aus.  In "
"<literal>Core::Ticket</literal> finden Sie die Option <literal>Ticket::"
"ArchiveSystem</literal>, die standardmäßig auf \"Nein\" steht. Ändern Sie "
"diese auf \"Ja\" und speichern Sie die Änderung ab."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:240
msgid "Define a GenericAgent job"
msgstr "Anlegen eines GenericAgent-Jobs"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:243
msgid "On the Admin page, select GenericAgent and add a new job there."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:249
msgid "Job Settings"
msgstr "Job-Einstellungen"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:252
msgid ""
"Provide a name for the archiving job, and select proper options to schedule "
"this job."
msgstr "Geben Sie dem Job einen geeigneten Namen und angemessene Optionen."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:258
msgid "Ticket Filter"
msgstr "Ticket-Filter"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:261
msgid ""
"The ticket filter is searches for tickets that match the selected criteria. "
"It might be a good idea to only archive those tickets in a closed state that "
"have been closed a few months before."
msgstr ""
"Der Ticketfilter ist eine Ticketsuche, die Tickets nach bestimmten Kriterien "
"auswählt. Es könnte empfehlenswert sein, nur Tickets zu archivieren, die "
"seit einigen Monaten im Status \"geschlossen\" sind."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:268
msgid "Ticket Action"
msgstr "Ticket-Aktion"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:271
msgid ""
"In this section, set the field labeled \"Archive selected tickets\" to "
"\"archive tickets\"."
msgstr ""
"Im Abschnitt \"Ticket-Aktion\" werden Sie eine Aktion \"Ausgewählte Tickets "
"archivieren\" finden. Wählen Sie dort \"Tickets archivieren\" aus."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:277
msgid "Save the job"
msgstr "Job speichern"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:280
msgid "At the end of the page you will find an option to save the job."
msgstr "Am Ende der Seite finden Sie einen Knopf zum Speichern des Jobs."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:285
msgid "Affected tickets"
msgstr "Betroffene Tickets"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:288
msgid ""
"The system will display all tickets which will be archived when executing "
"the Generic Agent job."
msgstr ""
"Das System wird dann alle Tickets anzeigen, die beim Ausführen des "
"GenericAgent-Jobs archiviert werden."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:297
msgid "Ticket Search"
msgstr "Ticketsuche"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:300
msgid ""
"When you search for tickets, the system default is to search tickets which "
"are not archived. If you want to search through archived tickets also, "
"simply add \"archive search\" while defining search criteria."
msgstr ""
"Wenn Sie nun nach Tickets suchen, werden standardmäßig nur Tickets gefunden, "
"die nicht archiviert sind. Wenn Sie auch in archivierten Tickets suchen "
"wollen, fügen Sie \"Archivsuche\" zu Ihren Suchkriterien hinzu."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:308
msgid "Cache"
msgstr "Cache"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:310
msgid ""
"OTRS caches a lot of temporary data in <filename>/opt/otrs/var/tmp</"
"filename>. Please make sure that this uses a high performance file system/"
"storage. If you have enough RAM, you can also try to put this directory on a "
"ramdisk like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:315
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Session::DeleteAll\n"
"shell> /opt/otrs/bin/otrs.Console.pl Maint::Cache::Delete\n"
"shell> sudo mount -o size=16G -t tmpfs none /opt/otrs/var/tmp\n"
"\n"
"# add persistent mount point in /etc/fstab\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:325
msgid ""
"Please note that this will be a non-permanent storage that will be lost on "
"server reboot. All your sessions (if you store them in the filesystem) and "
"your cache data will be lost."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:330
msgid ""
"There is also a centralized memcached based cache backend available for "
"purchase from OTRS Group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:338
msgid "Database"
msgstr "Datenbank"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:340
msgid ""
"DB issues vary by the database being used. Study the documentation for your "
"database or check with your database administrator."
msgstr ""
"Einstellungen sind immer spezifisch für die jeweils eingesetzte Datenbank. "
"Bei Problemen lesen Sie die Dokumentation und fragen Sie Ihren "
"Datenbankadministrator."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:347
msgid ""
"If you use the MySQL table type MyISAM (which is the default), and have "
"deleted a large part of a table or if you have made many changes to a table "
"with variable-length rows (tables that have VARCHAR, BLOB or TEXT columns), "
"you must defragment the datafile (tables) with the \"optimize\" command."
msgstr ""
"Wenn Sie den Tabellentyp MyISAM (Standard) benutzen, und einen großen Teil "
"einer Tabelle gelöscht haben, oder wenn Sie sehr viele Änderungen an einer "
"Tabelle mit Zeilen variabler Länge vorgenommen haben (Tabellen mit VARCHAR, "
"BLOB oder TEXT Spalten), sollten Sie die Datendateien (Tabellen) mit dem "
"\"optimize\" Kommando behandeln."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:352
msgid ""
"You should try this if the mysqld daemon needs a lot of your CPU time. "
"Optimize the tables - ticket, ticket_history and article (see Script below)."
msgstr ""
"Dies bietet sich an, wenn MySQL viel CPU Zeit braucht. Optimieren Sie die "
"Tabellen ticket, ticket_history und article."

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:356
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"shell> mysql -u user -p database\n"
"mysql> optimize table ticket;\n"
"mysql> optimize table ticket_history;\n"
"mysql> optimize table article;\n"
msgstr ""
"shell> mysql -u user -p database\n"
"mysql> optimize table ticket;\n"
"mysql> optimize table ticket_history;\n"
"mysql> optimize table article;\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:364
msgid "<emphasis>Script: Optimizing data base tables.</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>Skript: Optimierung von Datenbanktabellen.</emphasis>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/content/performance-tuning.xml:371
msgid ""
"PostgreSQL is best tuned by modifying the <filename>postgresql.conf</"
"filename> file in your PostgreSQL data directory. For advice on how to do "
